article.description: Desi Washington leads St. Peter's over Monmouth 62-61 in OT
article.headline: Desi Washington leads St. Peter's over Monmouth 62-61 in OT
article.linkText: Desi Washington leads St. Peter's over Monmouth 62-61 in OT
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- Desi Washington scored 21, including two free throws with 1:04 left in overtime, to help St. Peter's hold off Monmouth 62-61 on Wednesday night. Washington's free throws capped the scoring for the Peacocks (9-9, 3-4 Metro Atlantic) with a three-point lead. Justin Robinson pulled Monmouth (8-9, 5-2) within 62-61 on a pair of free throws with 52 seconds left. Robinson's steal with 29 seconds left set the Hawks up with a final shot to win, but Andrew Nicholas' jumper was off in the final seconds. Robinson scored 22 and Nicholas 17 to lead the Hawks. Washington made it 50-42 on a jumper with 3:19 left in regulation. The Hawks answered with a 10-2 run to force overtime. Saint Peter's opened the game missing its first 12 field goals and Monmouth started 2 of 10 from the field. The Hawks led just 6-3 with 10 minutes left in the first half.
